To create a C program for Raspberry Pi Zero W that detects motion using a HC-SR501 PIR sensor on GPIO 17 and logs timestamped HIGH/LOW state changes to 'motion.log', you can use the `wiringPi` library. Here's a sample program:

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <unistd.h>
#include <time.h>
#include <wiringPi.h>

#define PIR_SENSOR_PIN 17
#define LOG_FILE "motion.log"

